  AnswerChoices: 50-th; 25-th; 95-th; I can't tell
  CorrectAnswer: 50-th
  AnswerTests: omnitest(correctExpr='50-th')
  Hint: The median is the point at which half of the outcomes are above and half are below.

- Class: text
  Output: Remember, when we're talking about medians we're referring to population quantities. A probability model connects the data to the population using assumptions. Therefore the  the sample median will be the estimator of the  population median (the estimand).

